topPRs.title: Add AI Gateway Plugin to ElizaOS Registry
topPRs.author: Dexploarer
topPRs.body:
## Summary
• Add @elizaos-plugins/plugin-aigateway to the plugin registry
• Universal AI Gateway integration plugin for elizaOS
• Provides access to 100+ AI models through unified gateways

## Plugin Details
- **Repository**: https://github.com/dexploarer/plugin-aigateway
- **Package**: @elizaos/plugin-aigateway
- **Version**: 1.0.0
- **Features**: Text generation, image generation, embeddings, model listing
- **Supported Gateways**: Vercel AI Gateway, OpenRouter, and custom gateways

## Quality Assurance
✅ All tests pass (25/25)
✅ Clean TypeScript build
✅ Code formatted with prettier
✅ No console.log statements in production code
✅ Follows ElizaOS plugin architecture

<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

## Summary by CodeRabbit

- Documentation
  - Added RSS feed plugin to the Available Plugins list in README.

- Chores
  - Updated registry metadata: added @elizaos-plugins/plugin-rss-feed, @elizaos/plugin-twitter-rss, and @elizaos-plugins/plugin-aigateway.
  - Bumped patch versions for multiple plugins and removed several v1 branch pins.
  - Adjusted supports flags and updated last updated timestamp.
  - Expanded index with mappings for the new plugins.

<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

topPRs.title: Add plugin-fal-ai to registry
topPRs.author: yungalgo
topPRs.body:
This PR adds plugin-fal-ai to the registry.

- Package name: plugin-fal-ai
- GitHub repository: github:yungalgo/plugin-fal-ai
- Version: 0.1.0
- Description: ElizaOS plugin for fal-ai

Submitted by: @yungalgo

<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

## Summary by CodeRabbit

* **New Features**
  * Added the Fal AI plugin to the public plugin catalog, making it available for discovery, installation, and use.
  * Users can now enable Fal AI capabilities through the plugin system, just like other available plugins.
  * The plugin appears alongside existing entries in the plugin listing; no changes to existing plugins’ availability or behavior.
